  "verdict_html": "<ul><li><b>DOES NOT SHIP.</b> Failing gates: net Sharpe 2.337 &lt; 6.0.</li><li><b>Vs EXP-2730 (net Sharpe 6.164 baseline).</b> Static mix net Sharpe 2.337 trails the risk-parity v8a baseline by -3.827. The static mix does not expand the Sharpe buffer above the 6.0 ship gate.</li><li><b>Capacity binding stream:</b> <b>xlf_cs</b> \u2014 at 100% of its $30.0M hard cap, the portfolio is $300.0M AUM. To scale beyond this, the xlf_cs weight must be cut OR its hard cap lifted (backfill / strike staggering).</li><li><b>SPY weekly contribution.</b> At 15% weight and ~$7.6B hard cap, spy_wk contributes $1.1B of portfolio AUM headroom \u2014 4\u00d7 the $200M target. It is NOT the binding stream at this weight; the binding constraint is the old thin chains (XLF/XLI) which still cap the book. Reducing XLF/XLI further would unlock more headroom, but the task pinned them at 10%/3%.</li></ul>"
